## 📁 FTP (File Transfer Protocol) — Footprinting Notes

FTP is a standard protocol used to transfer files between a client and server over a network. It operates on **port 21** for control and **port 20** for data in active mode.

---

### 📡 Ports Used

| Port | Usage               |
|------|---------------------|
| 21   | Command/control     |
| 20   | Data transfer (active mode) |

> ✅ FTP is the only protocol among common services that uses **two ports** simultaneously.

---

### 🚀 Basic FTP Sign-in Procedure

To connect to an FTP server:
```bash
ftp <target> -p <port>

